        <div class="modal-body">
          <p>Blackjack, also known as twenty-one, is the most widely played casino card game in the world. Players compete against the dealer but, not against other players. This version is played with one deck of 52 cards, one player and a dealer.</p>
          <p>The player is dealt an initial two-card hand and the score is computed by adding the value of the cards. Face cards (kings, queens, and jacks) are counted as ten points. Aces count as 1 point or 11 points. All other cards are counted as the numeric value shown on the card. After receiving their initial two cards, the player has the options of "hitting" (taking an additional card) or “staying” (keeping their given cards). The dealer has to hit until their cards total 17 or more points.</p>
          <p>In a given round, the player or the dealer wins by having a score of 21 or by having the highest score that is less than 21. Scoring higher than 21 (called "busting" or "going bust") results in a loss. A player may win by having any final score equal to or less than 21 if the dealer busts. A tie is declared when the player and dealer have the same point total. The outcome of a tie can differ by house rules. In this version, a tie results in a win for the dealer with one exception: if the player’s initial two cards result in a blackjack (score of 21), then the player wins regardless of the dealer’s hand.</p>
        </div>
